import React from 'react';
export const Logo: React.FC<{ className?: string }> = () => null;

The error "Function setDoc() called with invalid data. Unsupported field value: undefined" occurs because Firebase Firestore does not accept `undefined` as a value for fields (like `photoUrl` when no photo is taken).

I will fix this by sanitizing the data objects (removing `undefined` fields) before sending them to Firebase in `services/storageService.ts`. This ensures that optional fields like `photoUrl` are handled correctly.

